<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!DOCTYPE plist PUBLIC "-//Apple//DTD PLIST 1.0//EN" "http://www.apple.com/DTDs/PropertyList-1.0.dtd">
<!--
    GPXEditor.Debug.entitlements

    The Debug-configuration variant of the application's entitlements.  Loaded
    via the per-configuration CODE_SIGN_ENTITLEMENTS build setting, which points
    at GPXEditor.entitlements for Release and at this file for Debug.

    What this file contains: every entitlement from the production file (which
    is the source of truth — see SECURITY.md "Sandbox entitlements"), PLUS
    one Hardened Runtime exception that is required during development with
    a self-signed code-signing certificate (D-019):

        com.apple.security.cs.disable-library-validation

    Why the exception is needed:  Hardened Runtime's library validation
    requires every dynamic library loaded into the host process to have a
    matching TeamIdentifier in its code signature.  Self-signed certificates
    do not carry a TeamIdentifier (the value is literally "not set"), and
    "not set" does not count as a positive match — even when the host and
    the loaded library are signed with the exact same self-signed cert.
    The result is that XCTest test bundles cannot be loaded into the host
    app process at test time, which breaks the entire test suite under
    self-signed signing.

    Disabling library validation in Debug only restores test loading without
    weakening the production posture.  The Release-configuration build
    continues to use GPXEditor.entitlements (no exception), so the shipped
    binary's Hardened Runtime stays strict.

    This entire file disappears at M10 when the project switches to a
    Developer ID Application certificate.  At that point CODE_SIGN_ENTITLEMENTS
    can be reverted to a single file, library validation re-enables for Debug,
    and SECURITY.md's invariant ("no Hardened Runtime exception entitlements
    are granted") is fully restored.

    Any change to this file requires a same-commit update to SECURITY.md.
-->
<plist version="1.0">
<dict>
    <!--
        Same as GPXEditor.entitlements.  Enables App Sandbox.  Mandatory for
        the project per SECURITY.md and per Decision D-007's posture statement.
    -->
    <key>com.apple.security.app-sandbox</key>
    <true/>

    <!--
        Same as GPXEditor.entitlements.  Allows the app to read user-chosen
        files via NSOpenPanel.
    -->
    <key>com.apple.security.files.user-selected.read-only</key>
    <true/>

    <!--
        Same as GPXEditor.entitlements.  Allows the app to write to user-
        chosen files via NSSavePanel.
    -->
    <key>com.apple.security.files.user-selected.read-write</key>
    <true/>

    <!--
        Same as GPXEditor.entitlements.  Allows outbound network connections
        for tile servers and the elevation API.  Per-domain enforcement is
        implemented in application code (NetworkAllowList, WKContentRuleList).
    -->
    <key>com.apple.security.network.client</key>
    <true/>

    <!--
        Debug-only Hardened Runtime exception.  Disables library validation
        so XCTest can dlopen the test bundle into the host process when both
        are signed with a self-signed certificate that has no TeamIdentifier.
        Required only during the D-019 self-signed development era; absent
        from GPXEditor.entitlements (the Release file) so the shipped binary
        retains strict library validation.

        Removed at M10 along with the switch to Developer ID Application
        signing — see SECURITY.md "Code signing and notarization".
    -->
    <key>com.apple.security.cs.disable-library-validation</key>
    <true/>
</dict>
</plist>
